In [45]:

import pandas as pd

sns.violinplot(x='income', y='age', data=train_df, palette="Set3")
plt.title('age vs income');

Signal :

  1. The proportion USA population earning less than 50K is more across all workclass
  2. The proportion USA population earning more than 50K is more in Self employed segment
In [47]:
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

 
sns.countplot(y='workclass', hue='income', data=train_df, palette="viridis")
plt.title('Distribution of income vs workclass in training set');

Signal :

  1. Most categories earn less than 50K which is similar to overall trend
  2. Work population who has masters, doctorate or have gone to professional school earns mostly above 50K
  3. Work population who have 12th or lesser educational degree earns less than 50K
In [48]:

Signal :

  1. The USA population earning more than 50K works for more hours
  2. Income doesn't have any direct proportionality with hours_per_week
